<br>
<br> Director of Programs 
<br>
<br> Silicon Valley Education Foundation (SV[e]F) is the largest educational nonprofit in Silicon Valley. Our mission is to deliver and advocate for STEM education that inspires students, who lack access and opportunities, to succeed in college and careers. We are guided by the belief that all students are capable of pursuing higher education and boosting their future economic mobility regardless of their background. SV[e]F has an established legacy of providing proven STEM programs and being profoundly committed to empowering students to graduate high school career and college ready. The impact of our work is evident in our strong partnerships with districts and donors in closing the achievement gap and the creation of a workforce that has the skills to meet 21st century needs. 
<br>
<br> POSITION SUMMARY 
<br>
<br> The Director of Programs is responsible for the overall development, management, and direction of the 
<br>
<br> Eastside Education Initiative (EEI) and Elevate [Math] (EM) programs, in addition to overseeing the operations 
<br>
<br> of SV[e]F STEM programs that include Computer Science (CS) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). Duties include 
<br>
<br> day-to-day operations, management of staff, program design, implementation, milestone creation/tracking, 
<br>
<br> curriculum management and school district communications of program evaluation, co-developing and 
<br>
<br> monitoring of the budget, participating in obtaining funds/grants, and coordinating/integrating programs with 
<br>
<br> other SV[e]F initiatives. The Director of Programs reports to the Chief Programs Officer (CPO) and works closely 
<br>
<br> with other SV[e]F Directors to lead and champion SV[e]Fs mission and services. 
<br>
<br> MAJOR DUTIES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES 
<br>
<br> Strategic Planning &amp; Leadership 
<br>
<br> <b>Work collaboratively with the CPO to:</b>
<br> Develop a comprehensive, long-term vision and strategy for EM and EEI, integrating both programs to leverage shared goals and objectives. 
<br>
<br> Design engaging and transformative EM and EEI learning experiences, including curriculum and teachers professional learning, for multiple grade levels and instructors alike. 
<br>
<br> Co-Design and implement AI related learning experiences in EM and EEI including curriculum and teachers professional learning, for multiple grade levels and educators. 
<br>
<br> Develop and track key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure program impact and outcomes, providing regular progress updates to stakeholders, including school districts, partners, and the community, to ensure transparency and accountability. 
<br>
<br> Identify innovative methods to continue to develop, add services and scale programs in participating districts and replicate them with new districts, promoting expansion and growth. 
<br>
<br> Lead strategy discussions, implementation, and organizational/infrastructure planning for Elevate Math and EEI, ensuring seamless integration and alignment. 
<br>
<br> Develop multi-year program milestones and objectives as well as day-to-day workflows and plans to achieve goals. 
<br>
<br> Lead cross-functional teams, including staff, partners, and stakeholders through collective impact practices to drive results. 
<br>
<br> Provide leadership in the implementation of strategic initiatives to continually refine and improve SV[e]F education programs (EM and EEI) while meeting measurable goals and objectives. 
<br>
<br> Present and attend regional education events, SV[e]F special events, and conferences on behalf of SV[e]F. 
<br>
<br> Operations Management 
<br>
<br> Collaborate and co-develop curriculum to integrate AI-infused learning and engagement experiences across EM and EEI curriculum for diverse grade levels, providing teachers with professional learning opportunities to ensure successful implementation. 
<br>
<br> Establish processes for program management  program development, preparation, execution and evaluation/reporting. 
<br>
<br> Lead day-to-day operations and implementation toward identified goals and yearly milestones. 
<br>
<br> Build and oversee recruitment, development and management of the Program team. 
<br>
<br> Analyze data to inform program decisions, measure program impact, and drive continuous improvement. 
<br>
<br> Lead and coordinate teacher professional learning opportunities of EM &amp; EEI programs curriculum on an ongoing basis. 
<br>
<br> Work collaboratively with District Partnerships staff to build relationships with participating school districts at multiple levels. 
<br>
<br> Work collaboratively with District Partnerships staff to negotiate the MOUs with the districts, including all financial and other commitments. 
<br>
<br> Ensure the consistent use of the SV[e]F customer relationship management system, G-Suite and other tools to ensure responsive year-round communication to key school district stakeholders, teachers, parents, and students regarding program start dates, end dates, registration, academic assessments, survey and SV[e]F aligned activities. 
<br>
<br> Establish relationships with other partners for building and sustaining programs. 
<br>
<br> People Management 
<br>
<br> Supervise, manage, and evaluate program managers and staff as indicated in the organizational chart. 
<br>
<br> Create a positive and productive work environment, foster collaboration, innovation and leadership. 
<br>
<br> Manage the support and engagement of staff development programs to enhance skills and abilities of 
<br>
<br> direct reports to provide for professional growth. 
<br>
<br> Financial Management 
<br>
<br> Work collaboratively with the CPO to develop and monitor the annual Programs budget and execute according to the plan. 
<br>
<br> Fundraising 
<br>
<br> Work collaboratively with District Partnership staff to develop and co-lead the fundraising for District 
<br>
<br> revenue for initiatives. 
<br>
<br> Actively participate in SV[e]Fs efforts to develop and implement activities to identify, solicit, involve and retain donors.
